        "right_video_url": "",
        "Heading_size": "h2",
        "Heading_color": "#f8f2e6",
        "title": "In The Celler",
        "video-sec-content-txt-1": "<p>To create this wine, Pinotage grapes were crushed and transferred to our winery’s traditional, open-top concrete fermentation tanks, constructed nearly a century ago by our founder, Albertus Viljoen van der Merwe (or ‘Oupa Alvi,’ as we still fondly refer to him).</p><p>During fermentation, punch-downs (<em>pigéage</em>) were performed by hand, up to eight times daily, to optimise skin-to-juice contact and enhance both colour and flavour extraction.</p><p>Following fermentation, the wine was left to soak on the skins for several days before being transferred to a combination of new French and American oak barrels. It was then matured for 12 months before final bottling.</p>",
        "button-txt": "",
        "button_link": "",
        "button_type": "alvisBtn"
      }
